To maximize the usefulness of this new knowledge and to facilitate its uptake by news media (which, in turn, is key to cultivating interest and attention among the public and government officials), one particular coordinated action from the existing international community of WBE scientists would be very useful and could catalyze a formalized effort for international coordination. This action would at first simply involve the creation of a web-based database that would serve as a clearing house for all existing and planned R&D activities surrounding the application of WBE to Covid-19 (and possibly other infectious diseases). This clearing house would be populated by information solicited from, or provided by, WBE principal investigators worldwide. As existing efforts to enhance collaboration and support of WBE Covid-19 research grow (e.g., 
 Bibby, 2020; 
 PÃ©rez-Escudero et al., 2020), they could be unified under a single umbrella.
